
@startuml

' Main classes
class Customer {
    +String name
    +String contactInfo
    +List<Car> registeredCars
}

class Car {
    +String licensePlate
    +String make
    +String model
    +String year
    +boolean isSelfDriving
    +Customer owner
}

class Ride {
    +LocalDateTime pickupTime
    +LocalDateTime dropoffTime
    +Location pickupLocation
    +Location dropoffLocation
    +Duration duration
    +double distance
    +int numberOfPassengers
    +double fee
    +String typeOfRequest
    +List<Customer> passengers
}

class RideHail extends Ride {
    +Customer leadCustomer
    +int maxPassengers
}

class RideShare extends Ride {
    +double negotiatedFeePerCustomer
    +int maxPassengers
    +int rideSharesBooked
    +int treesPlanted
}

class Accident {
    +LocalDate accidentDate
    +Location accidentLocation
    +double damageAmount
    +Car involvedCar
}

' Relationships
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Car : owns
Car "1" -- "1" Customer : ownedBy
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Ride : uses
Ride "1" -- "1" Car : uses
RideHail "1" -- "1" Ride : is a
RideShare "1" -- "1" Ride : is a
Car "1" -- "0..*" Accident : has

@enduml

### Notes:
- **Customer** can own one or more cars and can use rides (both hailing and sharing).
- **Car** can be either self-driving or registered by a customer.
- **Ride** is an abstract class with common attributes and methods for both ride types.
- **RideHail** and **RideShare** are concrete subclasses of `Ride` with specific attributes and constraints.
- **Accident** is a separate class to track incidents involving cars.

